cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on robust deep learning and proposes a new loss function for training DNNs. It also involves empirical analysis and experiments to evaluate the proposed method. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments involve image classification tasks. 

Additionally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of deep learning models. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as it involves training neural networks. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a less likely sub-category as it involves proposing a new method for weighting examples in the loss function, which could be seen as a data structure or algorithmic problem.
